caption: Figure 1: Results of bilevel optimization on deep AUC maximization. Figure (a), (b) are the results over epochs, and Figure (c), (d) are the results over running time.
description: This figure presents the results of applying bilevel optimization algorithms to a deep AUC maximization task.  Subfigures (a) and (b) display the training and test AUC scores, respectively, plotted against the number of training epochs.  Subfigures (c) and (d) show the same metrics but plotted against the running time of the algorithms.  The figure compares the performance of the proposed AccBO algorithm against several baselines, including StocBio, TTSA, SABA, MA-SOBA, SUSTAIN, VRBO, and BO-REP.  The results demonstrate that AccBO achieves higher AUC scores and faster convergence than the other methods.

caption: Figure 1: Results of bilevel optimization on deep AUC maximization. Figure (a), (b) are the results over epochs, and Figure (c), (d) are the results over running time.
description: The figure shows the performance of AccBO and other baseline algorithms on the deep AUC maximization task.  Figures (a) and (b) present the training and test AUC scores, respectively, plotted against the number of epochs (iterations). Figures (c) and (d) show the same metrics but plotted against the running time in seconds.  This comparison highlights AccBO's faster convergence and superior performance compared to the baselines in terms of both AUC score and computational efficiency.
